Animate.desc:
calls a function repeatedly like setInterval() but with the current time (Date.getTime()) and the difference to the last call in milliseconds as parameter
when using _AddOptions( "NoDom" ); to cause a high performance you can't use SetInterval but Animate.

comparison:

normal:
	setInterval: about 242 calls per second
	app.animate: about 217 calls per second

with "NoDom" option:
	setInterval: error
	app.Animate: max. 600-750 calls per second
Animate.name: Animate

	_globalAlpha: num_flt

	drawImage(image,sx,sy,sw,sh,dx,dy,dw,dh)
	loadTexture(image,successCallback,errorCallback)
	render()
	resetTransform()
	restore()
	rotate(angle)
	save()
	scale(a,d)
	setTransform(a,b,c,d,tx,ty)
	transform(a,b,c,d,tx,ty)
	translate(tx,ty)
	unloadTexture(image)
}
